etymology.description: 亻(亻) (rén, "person") + 吾(吾) (wú, "I") = person-related action involving oneself -> not a standard character
etymology.interpretation: The character is composed of the person radical 亻(亻) and 吾(吾), suggesting an action or state concerning oneself. It is not commonly used in modern Chinese and does not have a standard meaning.
